Edgar Howard Wright -LRB- born 18 April 1974 -RRB- is an English director , screenwriter , producer , and actor .
He is best known for his comedic Three Flavours Cornetto film trilogy consisting of Shaun of the Dead -LRB- 2004 -RRB- , Hot Fuzz -LRB- 2007 -RRB- , and The World 's End -LRB- 2013 -RRB- , made with recurrent collaborators Simon Pegg , Nira Park and Nick Frost .
He also collaborated with them as the director of the television series Spaced .
He also co-wrote , produced and directed the 2010 film Scott Pilgrim vs. the World .
Along with his friends Joe Cornish and Steven Moffat , he co-wrote Steven Spielberg 's The Adventures of Tintin : The Secret of the Unicorn .
Wright and Cornish co-wrote the screenplay for the Marvel Studios film Ant-Man , which Wright was intended to direct before departing the project .